NEWCASTLE DISEASE, POULTRY - PERU: (TACNA) OIE
**********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Wed 22 Apr 2009
Source: OIE WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly
disease information 2009; 22(17) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>


Newcastle disease, Peru
-----------------------
Information received on 22 Apr 2009 from Mr Oscar Miguel Dominguez Falcon,
SENASA [national agrarian health service], [director general for animal
health], Lima, Peru

Summary
Report type: immediate notification (final report)
Start date: 25 Feb 2009
Date of first confirmation of the event: 9 Mar 2009
Report date: 21 Apr 2009
Date submitted to OIE: 22 Apr 2009
Date event resolved: 18 Mar 2009
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 1995
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: avian paramyxovirus type 1 (APMV-1)
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 (027.09.00010) El Alto de la Alianza, Tacna, Tacna, Tacna
Date of start of the outbreak: 25 Feb 2009
Outbreak status: resolved (18 Mar 2009)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Species: birds
Susceptible: --
Cases: 13
Deaths: 8
Destroyed: 25
Slaughtered: 0
Affected population: backyard poultry

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak statistics
Species: birds
Apparent morbidity rate: **
Apparent mortality rate: **
Apparent case fatality rate: 62 per cent
Proportion susceptible animals lost*: **
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction,
and/or slaughter
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: introduction of new live
animals. Fomites (humans, vehicles, feed, etc.)
Epidemiological comments: the outbreak was reported by the poultry's owner.
It was put under control by culling all the birds in the affected farm. A
ring vaccination was applied. All poultry farms and establishments within a
10 km [6.2 mi] radius were evaluated and no evidence of the disease was
found. No new cases have occurred and no birds have been present on the
farm since more than 30 days. Cleaning and disinfection have been carried
out. The outbreak is considered resolved.

Control measures
Measures applied:
- stamping out
- quarantine
- movement control inside the country
- screening
- zoning
- disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s)
- no treatment of affected animals
- vaccination in response to the outbreak (s):

Administrative division: Tacna
Species: birds
Total vaccinated: 11 822
Details: live vaccine type V
Measures to be applied
No other measures
Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: SENASA (National Agrarian Health Service)
(national laboratory)
Tests and results
Species: birds
Test: reverse transcription - polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR)
Test date: 9 Mar 2009
Result: negative
Species: birds
Test: virus isolation
Test date: 9 Mar 2009
Result: positive
Laboratory name and type National Veterinary Services Laboratories, Ames
(Iowa, United States) (OIE's reference laboratory)
Species: birds
Test: real-time PCR
Test date: 17 Apr 2009
Result: positive
Species: birds
Test: virus isolation
Test date: 17 Apr 2009
Result: positive
Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Between 2005 and 2009, Peru only reported 2 outbreaks occurring in 2008 in
the administrative divisions of Arequipa and Cusco. - Mod.PC

The OIE report at the URL above includes a map with the location of the
outbreak in southern Peru. The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of
Peru is available at <http://healthmap.org/r/00a3>. - CopyEd.MJ]
